title: Miami pushes FSU K Roberto Aguayo before game (Video)
text:
Miami pushes FSU K Roberto Aguayo before game (Video) October 10, 2015 0 0 
Just in case you thought the rivalry between Miami and Florida State had simmered down, here’s a good reminder that it remains as heated as ever. 
Prior to Saturday’s contest in Tallahassee, Seminoles kicker Roberto Aguayo apparently crossed over into Hurricanes territory during warmups. Miami was quick to show him he was somewhere he didn’t belong, and one player even got physical with the kicker: Oh boy. #Canes not happy #FSU kicker Aguayo was on their side of the field warming up. They let him know it. pic.twitter.com/UngYp6gEW5 
— Will Manso (@WillManso) October 10, 2015 
The ‘Noles have won the last five meetings between the teams, including eight of the last ten. You better believe that they won’t let themselves get pushed around during the actual game. Filed Under:
